article.headline: Arkansas 90, Texas Southern 40
article.story:
FAYETTEVILLE, Ark. (AP) -- Leslie Howard's 17 points paced
Arkansas to a 90-40 win Sunday over Texas Southern.

Howard was 6-of-9 from the field, hitting 5-of-8 of her shots
from 3-point range.

The Lady Razorbacks (9-1) led 48-25 at the half after holding
Texas Southern (1-5) to just 33 percent shooting. Arkansas then
widened the gap in the second half by improving its field-goal
shooting from 48 percent before intermission to 51 percent
afterward, while allowing the visitors to make just 19 percent of
their shots.

Taneisha Riles led Texas Southern with 12 points.

Donica Cosby added 13 points for Arkansas, while Lauren Ervin
scored 12 and Tanisha Smith had 11. Brittney Vaughn was credited
with 11 assists.
